xf86-video-vpro - SGI Odyssey (VPro) video driver for the Xorg X server

The Odyssey (a.k.a. VPro, "Buzz"/"PB&J") is the graphics board of the SGI
Octane2 / late Octane (IP30) workstations.  Unlike older SGI graphics it
exposes no CPU-visible linear framebuffer: it is a dual-chip OpenGL engine
programmed entirely through a command FIFO.

This driver therefore:

  * relies on the kernel `odyssey' fbdev driver to program the panel timing
    and to expose the register window via /dev/fbN (mmap offset 0);
  * renders the desktop into a host-side shadow framebuffer using the
    normal Xorg fb layer;
  * uploads the dirty regions of that shadow into the board's VRAM through
    the command FIFO (glDrawPixels-style PIO blit) via the ShadowFB hooks.

The low-level command-FIFO engine (hardware bring-up, solid rectangles and
lines, pixel upload and screen-to-screen copy) lives in src/vpro_accel.c and
was ported from the Linux odyssey fbdev driver and the IRIX Odyssey PROM
textport code.

Only the fixed 1280x1024 24bpp (packed 32bpp) TrueColor mode is supported.

See XF86Config.vpro for an example configuration.
